00:27:02.567 --> 00:27:03.900
And you don't want that, anyway.

00:27:06.410 --> 00:27:10.909
OK, so let us see
what happens here.

00:27:10.909 --> 00:27:11.950
And so let's get to work.

00:27:16.010 --> 00:27:25.510
Suppose we have an electronic
state 1s alpha spin.

00:27:25.510 --> 00:27:29.110
We know alpha is
ms equals plus 1/2.

00:27:29.110 --> 00:27:31.390
And beta is ms equals minus 1/2.

00:27:36.920 --> 00:27:40.580
So this is the
spatial coordinate.

00:27:40.580 --> 00:27:43.120
This is the spin coordinate.

00:27:43.120 --> 00:27:55.507
And, OK, so here is a simple
product of two wave functions.

00:27:55.507 --> 00:27:56.590
And we know what they are.

00:27:59.830 --> 00:28:18.720
And so if we apply p12 to this,
we get psi 1s alpha r2 sigma

00:28:18.720 --> 00:28:28.070
2 1s beta r1 sigma 1.

00:28:28.070 --> 00:28:30.500
We don't even know what
