00:28:43.210 --> 00:28:45.550
So weird, but they
are eigenfunctions

00:28:45.550 --> 00:28:50.070
of the zero-order Hamiltonian.

00:28:50.070 --> 00:28:53.010
So we can take a linear
combination of eigenfunctions

00:28:53.010 --> 00:28:55.810
that belong to the
same eigenvalue,

00:28:55.810 --> 00:28:58.250
and it's still the same energy.

00:28:58.250 --> 00:28:59.960
So we do that.

00:28:59.960 --> 00:29:10.630
And so what we can do is write
a combination of this function

00:29:10.630 --> 00:29:12.690
and that function.

00:29:12.690 --> 00:29:20.450
And if we do that, so now
we can have psi 1s 2s.

00:29:20.450 --> 00:29:24.050
And what we get is 1 over
the square root over 2

00:29:24.050 --> 00:29:25.780
for normalization.

00:29:25.780 --> 00:29:41.542
And we have psi 1s alpha r1
sigma 1 minus psi 1s beta

00:29:41.542 --> 00:29:45.010
